{"TopicId":212410,"ForumId":120,"TopicTitle":"Improve runway lights at night","CreatedByName":"Thundy","CreatedById":208895,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-24T19:03:03Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Thundy","CreatedById":208895,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-24T19:03:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRunway lights are not visible from long distances\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere is an image of the lights up close, it\u0027s okay, the brightness needs to be brightened up\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022G4a1Xgi.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022120.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/G4a1Xgi.jpg\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere is an image of it from far away:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00222vd4da3.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022120.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/2vd4da3.jpg\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIdeally it should look like the following\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/fCvb5zPCcqw?feature=oembed\u0022 title=\u0022Cockpit A320 | Night Landing in Frankfurt | Microsoft Flight Simulator 2020\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nAfter some analysis, it appears that while the lights exist, they have no lens-flair, or blur, or anything similar, some sort of particle that is displayed in place of the lights should work fairly well.\u003Cbr\u003E\nAlso, it would be great if it is viewable from space, that will immensely help \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E/Shuttle landings.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}